{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"baking paper, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), plastic wrap, silicone bread mat, serrated bread knife, wire rack, sealable container, oven, refrigerator","id":"r89703","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-SbfrD95tng4\/XZWqmpHMBbI\/AAAAAAAAfac\/40MevmEXoDQ5LBBHC37eNvY_yS5kgU-QACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_QrTOF1oRurexbDF-.png","title":"Red and green Christmas shortbread","publishedAt":"2015-12-14T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"40 g white rice"},{"content":"60 g raw sugar"},{"content":"300 g plain flour"},{"content":"250 g butter, cut into cubes"},{"content":"100 g shelled and unsalted pistachios"},{"content":"100 g dried cranberries"},{"content":"300 g white chocolate, broken into pieces"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"2.6 g","fat":"12 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"18 g","calories":"792 kJ \/ 189 kcal"},"preparations":[{"content":"Preheat oven to 150°C. Line a baking tray (30 x 40  cm) with baking paper and set aside."},{"content":"Place rice and sugar into the mixing bowl and mill <b>1 min\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add flour and butter and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>, then knead <b>40 sec\/<b>."},{"content":"Add pistachios and dried cranberries and chop <b>Turbo\/1 sec\/3-4 times<b>, until a roughly chopped yet even consistency is achieved."},{"content":"Transfer mixture onto a silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface and work mixture into a log (30 cm long). Wrap in plastic wrap and place in refrigerator for 1 hour to rest. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Remove from refrigerator, then using a serrated bread knife, cut into round slices (approx. 0.5 cm thick) to form biscuits. Place biscuits onto prepared baking tray and bake for approx. 20-30 minutes (150°C), or until biscuits are lightly golden."},{"content":"Leave shortbread to cool on baking tray for 10 minutes before transferring onto a wire rack to cool completely."},{"content":"While shortbread is cooling, place white chocolate into mixing bowl and grate <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then melt <b>3 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula again, then melt for a further <b>5-7 min\/37°C\/speed 1<b>, or until chocolate has completely melted."},{"content":"Once shortbread has cooled, dip half of each biscuit into the melted chocolate. Place dipped shortbread onto a plate or tray lined with baking paper, then transfer into the refrigerator until chocolate has set (approx. 30 minutes)."},{"content":"Serve immediately or transfer into a sealable container to store until use."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Baked shortbread will freeze well and can be dipped in the white chocolate while frozen. They will keep for up to 3 months in a freezable container in the freezer."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","2h 20m","30 pieces"]}